The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Advani beats Loong
New Delhi: World IBSF champion Pankaj Advani blanked John Loh ei Loong of Malaysia to stay on course for a clean sweep in group D in the World under-21 snooker championship in Carlow, Ireland. Advani, who has lost just four frames in his six matches so far, had no problem in thrashing Loong 69-19, 86-19, 73-48, 76-19, according to information received here., Aditya Mehta and Sourav Kothari will have to win both their remaining matches to keep their chances of making it to the knock-out stage alive. (PTI)  Copyright 
